# `ptr<ptr_i64>` — a box's ADDRESS — is coherent on all four tiers, and this
# fixture is the over-refusal control that keeps it that way.
#
# `addr_of(a)` over a `ptr_i64` place yields `ptr<ptr_i64>`: the outer type is a
# modern address (the stack slot holding the box), the pointee is a legacy box.
# Reading it back reproduces each tier's OWN faithful box — a heap-slot index on
# the interpreters, a machine address natively — because `ptr_read` of a
# box-typed cell REPRODUCES a box rather than REINTERPRETING one. Nothing here
# crosses the model boundary, so every tier agrees on 7.
#
# This is the exact program that decides how the `ptr_cast(addr_of(box))` hole
# had to be fixed. Two candidate fixes were on the table:
#
#   * refuse `addr_of` over a `ptr_T` place outright, or
#   * refuse only the model-crossing REINTERPRETATION.
#
# The first would reject THIS file, which is measurably correct on all four
# tiers — so it was rejected as over-refusal. The rule shipped instead is
# `mentions_box_model` in `semantics_raw_ptr.rs`: a box model is opaque at any
# nesting depth and may be reinterpreted neither FROM nor INTO, while the types
# themselves stay usable. This fixture pins the "stay usable" half; suite21's
# nested-launder tests pin the "refused" half.
#
# If a later change makes this file fail, the fix over-refused: it broke a
# coherent program to close an incoherent one. Rewrite the rule, not this file.
#
# NO `dealloc` HERE, deliberately: `dealloc` is not lowered natively (a native
# free cannot reproduce the interpreters' L0406 use-after-free detection), so a
# function using it is L0339-skipped and runs on the interpreters only. Since the
# whole point of this fixture is that NATIVE agrees with the interpreters, adding
# `dealloc` would silently reduce it to a three-tier test that no longer proves
# the thing it exists to prove. The single box is reclaimed at process exit.

fn main -> i64
    let a ptr_i64 = alloc(7)
    let value i64 = 0
    unsafe
        let pa ptr<ptr_i64> = addr_of(a)
        let back ptr_i64 = ptr_read(pa)
        value = ptr_read(back)
    value
